parts.text:
Fix these specific issues in Auth.css only. Do not touch any TSX files.

1. WAVEFORM BARS — increase contrast so they're visible:
   .wave-block         { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);  }
   .wave-block.tall    { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.95); }
   .wave-block.medium  { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); }
   .wave-block.short   { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.35); }

2. MOCK CARD title bars — make them visible:
   .mock-bar       { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);  }
   .mock-bar.short { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.45); }

3. REDUCE gap between pills and mock card:
   .mock-visual { margin-top: 1.5rem; }

4. FILL vertical space — push copyright to bottom,
   center the middle content:
   .auth-left {
     display: flex;
     flex-direction: column;
     justify-content: space-between;
     min-height: 100vh;
     padding: 3rem 2.5rem;
   }
   Wrap headline + subtext + pills + mock-visual 
   in a single .auth-left-content div if not already,
   so space-between pushes copyright to the very bottom.

5. FIX broken emoji in feature pills — replace emoji 
   characters with plain text icons using CSS ::before:
   Remove emoji from the TSX text content.
   Change the three feature items text to:
     "High-quality audio recording"
     "Video capture with live preview"  
     "AI assistant for your recordings"
   Add colored dot before each with CSS:
   .feature-item::before {
     content: '';
     width: 7px;
     height: 7px;
     border-radius: 50%;
     background: rgba(255,255,255,0.9);
     flex-shrink: 0;
   }

